      "name": "Weapon Group: Heavy Weapons",
      "type": "text",
      "title": {
        "show": false,
        "level": 1
      },
      "text": {
        "format": 1,
        "content": "<p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">These large weapon systems require a tripod, a base, a platform, or any other stable point from which to fire.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><strong style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Properties</strong>: Heavy weapons use the same general rules as ranged weapons, except as follows:<br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\" /></span></p>\n<ul style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813\">\n<li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Because of their cumbersome nature, if you move or are moved any distance you have disadvantage on attack rolls with heavy weapons until the beginning of your next turn.</span></li>\n<li style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">Unless mounted, heavy weapons require at least Strength 13 to use.<br style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\" /></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text;color:#191813\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing:border-box;user-select:text\">These weapons may be purchased for a Large user (e.g. exo-armor). If so, the heavy weapons counts as a two-handed weapon. It can no longer be used by Medium-sized users.</span></p>"
      },
